(Version 1.0) The data files below describe the SNP data used for the
paper "Haplotype variation and genotype imputation in African populations"
by L Huang, M Jakobsson, TJ Pemberton, M Ibrahim, T Nyambo, S Omar, 
JK Pritchard, SA Tishkoff, NA Rosenberg (Genetic Epidemiology 35(8):766-80
[2011]). These data are a combination of data from 8 African populations
and the data used for the paper "Using population mixtures to optimize the
utility of genomic databases: linkage disequilibrium and association study
design in India" by TJ Pemberton, M Jakobsson, DF Conrad, G Coop, JD Wall,
JK Pritchard, PI Patel, NA Rosenberg (Annals of Human Genetics 72:535-546
[2008]).

*Version 1.0 of the package of files - created by TJP, Jan 31, 2012

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

The following data sets are available:

1. unphased_HGDP+India+Africa_2810SNPs-regions1to36.stru
(HGDP data+Indian data+African data - 1107 individuals, 2810 SNPs)

2. phased_HGDP+India+Africa_2810SNPs-regions1to36.stru
(HGDP data+Indian data+African data - 1107 individuals, 2810 SNPs)

3. unphased_HGDP+India+Africa_1195SNPs-chr21-regions7to22.stru
(HGDP data+Indian data+African data - 1107 individuals, 1195 SNPs
on chromosome 21)

4. phased_HGDP+India+Africa_1272SNPs-chr21-regions7to22.stru
(HGDP data+Indian data+African data - 1107 individuals, 1272 SNPs
on chromosome 21)

5. unphased_HGDP+India+Africa_517SNPs-chr21-regions7to22.stru
(HGDP data+Indian data+African data - 1107 individuals, 517 SNPs
on chromosome 21)

6. phased_HapMap3-release2_517SNPs-chr21-regions7to22.stru
(HapMap Phase 3 release 2 data - 901 individuals, 517 SNPs
on chromosome 21)

7. chr21_hapmap3.polaritySNP
(44 SNP rs IDs)

File 1 is the raw HGDP, Indian, and African unphased data, after 
elimination of SNPs that failed quality checks and individuals who 
were related.

File 2 is the phased HGDP, Indian, and African data with all missing
genotypes imputed, using the genomic "regions" labels (1-36).

File 3 is the unphased HGDP, Indian, and African data for regions on
chromosome 21 only (7 to 22) and excluding the 77 SNPs masked for
the imputation analysis.

File 4 is the phased HGDP, Indian, and African data for regions on 
chromosome 21 only (7 to 22).

File 5 is the unphased HGDP, Indian, and African data after elimination
of SNPs that did not overlap with those of HapMap Phase 3 (release 2).

File 6 is the phased HapMap Phase 3 (release 2) data with all missing
genotypes imputed, for regions on chromosome 21 only (7 to 22).  This
file was created from the HapMap3 collection by leaving out individuals
who were related.

File 7 is a list of the 44 SNPs on chromosome 21 that were repolarized
in the HGDP+Indian+African data to match the HapMap data (see below).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

For 44 SNPs (see File 7), Files 1 and 2 appear to differ in strand
polarity from HapMap Phase 3 (release 2) - that is, for these SNPs, our
data arrived with a strand polarity different from that in the HapMap.
To create Files 3 to 6 that were analyzed in conjunction with the HapMap
data, these SNPs in the HGDP+Indian+African data were repolarized to match
the HapMap data.

Note that 3 of the core regions (regions 30, 31 and 32) contain large
gaps that we identified only after the design phase of the Conrad et
al. 2006 study was complete. For one analysis using core SNPs, we
split each of these regions into two regions. In this case, we
included 5 non-core SNPs (rs212858 in region 30, rs6467107 in region
32, rs6962580 in region 32, rs6467108 in region 32, and rs6467109 in
region 32) because each of these SNPs was located less than 200bp from
a core SNP or less than 200bp from a non-core SNP that was connected
to a core SNP by less than 200bp.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

The data are in "structure" format with 2 rows per individual.  

Rows:
1. rs number
2. region number (1..36)
3. chromosome number
4. snp position on chromosome
5. core region indicator (1 = core region, 0 = non-core region)
6...X*2+4: individual data for X individuals

In the phased files (Files 2, 4 and 6) each of the two rows for an
individual represents one of the two haplotypes.  Phasing was performed
within genomic regions, so there is no correspondence of haplotypes 
across region boundaries.  In the unphased files (Files 1, 3 and 5),
the placement of genotypes on the first versus second line for an
individual is arbitrary.

Columns for individual data (HGDP/India/Africa individuals):
1. HGDP ID number or HapMap NA number
2. numeric code for population
3. name of population
4. country of origin
5. geographic region of origin
6. ID number assigned during genotyping
7. sex (M = male, F = female)
8... genotypes (A, C, G, T, or ? for missing data or hemizygous males 
   on the X-chromosome)

Columns for individual data (HapMap individuals):
1. HapMap ID number (string)
2. numeric code for population
3. name of population
4. country of origin
5. geographic region of origin
6. HapMap ID number (string); a placeholder to make the number of columns
   match the HGDP/India/Africa data file
7. sex (M = male, F = female) taken from "Inference of unexpected genetic
   relatedness among individuals in HapMap Phase III" by TJ Pemberton,
   C Wang, JZ Li, NA Rosenberg (American Journal of Human Genetics 87(4):
   457-464 [2010]).
8... genotypes (A, C, G, T, or ? for missing data or hemizygous males 
   on the X-chromosome)
